   232	<threat_model>
   233	## Trust Boundaries
   234	
   235	| Boundary | Description |
   236	|----------|-------------|
   237	| Thermo RAW -> writer | RAW content is read-only input decoded by the vendor SDK; malformed scans already guarded by the Phase-2 per-scan try/catch + ParseInput.NewError(). |
   238	| writer -> .mzpeak archive | Output is a deterministic local file consumed by the reference reader / validator; no network, no untrusted consumer in this phase. |
   239	
   240	## STRIDE Threat Register
   241	
   242	| Threat ID | Category | Component | Disposition | Mitigation Plan |
   243	|-----------|----------|-----------|-------------|-----------------|
   244	| T-03-01 | Tampering | per-ordinal arrays vs four-table null discipline | mitigate | NUnit locks assert def-level discipline (precursor/selected_ion null on rows >= #MSn, count-null discipline) and source_index/precursor_index linkage via the scanNumber->ordinal map, preventing silently-misaligned tables. |
   245	| T-03-02 | Information disclosure | source RAW path in file_description.source_files[].location | accept | The location is the user-supplied input path written into the user's own output; no new exposure beyond existing TRFP behavior. |
   246	| T-03-03 | Denial of service | full in-memory accumulation of metadata for large RAW | accept | Inherited Phase-2 limitation (single row group, in-memory); large-RAW streaming is OPT/v2 scope, not regressed here. |
   247	| T-03-SC | Tampering | npm/pip/cargo installs | accept | Phase installs NO external packages (RESEARCH: Package Legitimacy Audit N/A); no new dependency surface. |
   248	</threat_model>
